  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge and open the packet to let it breathe before cooking</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Pull the<strong> chicken skin</strong> off the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> and season the <strong>chicken skin</strong> generously with <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641913643876-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641913643876-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641913643876-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641913643876-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641913643876-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chicken skin</strong> and fry for 7-8 min or until golden and beginning to crisp</p><p>Tip: Weigh the chicken skin down with a second, smaller pan to make it even crispier!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641913647708-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641913647708-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641913647708-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641913647708-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641913647708-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken skin is cooking, add the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> (use <strong>tin foil </strong>to avoid mess!)</p><p>Once the chicken skin is starting to crisp, add it to the tray with the chicken thighs and put the tray in the oven for 17-18 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641913689779-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641913689779-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641913689779-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641913689779-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641913689779-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and dice the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Slice the<strong> chestnut</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Strip the <strong>tarragon leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1641913698259-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1641913698259-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1641913698259-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1641913698259-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1641913698259-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced shallot</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced mushrooms </strong>and cook for 5 min further</p><p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> spaghetti</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> </strong>spaghetti for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite, then drain and set aside</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641913707238-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641913707238-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641913707238-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641913707238-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641913707238-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> with 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir through the <strong>soft cheese</strong> – this is your <strong>creamy chicken stock</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> kitchen paper</strong></p><p>Once the vegetables have softened, add the <strong>washed spinach</strong>, <strong>chopped tarragon</strong> (reserve a little for garnish) and <strong>creamy chicken stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 5 min further until the sauce has thickened</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1641913724303-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1641913724303-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1641913724303-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1641913724303-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1641913724303-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, remove the tray from the oven and shred it apart, using two forks – this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p><p>Add the <strong>shredded chicken</strong> and <strong>drained spaghetti</strong> to the pan and season with a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 min further until the sauce beings to stick to the pasta</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
